    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>Sept 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1858</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p>From every part of the <placeName>U States</placeName> Donations<lb/> are daily recd
                by our Various Benevolent<lb/> Institutions to assist their
                <sic>releiving</sic><lb/> the sick &amp; Indigent while religious<lb/> Institutions
                are also in receipt of<lb/> Various Sums to defray the Expense<lb/> of Burying the
                Dead These Donations<lb/> come from Christians to Christians<lb/> one House
                    (<sic>Jewellers</sic>) or our City<lb/> I forget the name (a Handsome white<lb/>
                marble Front Store on <placeName>Chestnut St</placeName>)<lb/> sent our Howard
                Association $500.00<lb/> I need not tell you How exhausted<lb/> any Treasury becomes
                when the<lb/> drain is constant for doctors<lb/> nurses medicines &amp;c. Our
                President<lb/> of the Gent Hebr. Ben Association<lb/>
                <persName>L B Cain Esq</persName> has worked hard &amp;<lb/> Business Health &amp;c
                is neglected<lb/> by him in his constant Labour<lb/> of seeing to the sick. Our congregation<lb/>
                <placeName>Rampart Sr.</placeName> has <sic>allready</sic> Buried<lb/> about 50 all
                Charity &amp; of course</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>a very Heavy outlay for their exhausted<lb/> Treasury, our “Home” must take<lb/> in a
                large number of orphans<lb/> left Destitute Oh its a sad scene<lb/> to witness &amp;
                I will not call up<lb/> the better feelings of your nature by<lb/> recounting all
                the misery<lb/> we witness here our Jewish<lb/> people of both sexes work<lb/> hard
                &amp; faithful &amp; are many<lb/> of them completely worn out!<lb/> The Fever still
                continues its<lb/> fatal work carrying off whole<lb/> &amp; frequently portions of a
                family.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Its to be hoped our <sic>Bretheren</sic><lb/> of your own admission
                Cities will<lb/> not wait a similar call to one<lb/> we made (&amp; I am happy to
                acknow<lb/>ledge not in vain) once before<lb/> but some Influential good
                    Philantro<lb/><sic>phists</sic> will be found to go to work &amp;<lb/> send some
                relief ere its too late<lb/> Excuse this hasty scrawl yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">ever Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName>
            </p>
            <p><persName>Mr DeSilva</persName> paid me $25.00 for the Hebrew Prayer Books (11)</p>
        </body>
